Commentary: hard length in the channel, Azam steps out and punches to extra cover
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: banged into the surface at 87mph/139kph and this is angled towards backward point with an open face
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short and at the body, 82mph/132kph and worked through square off the back foot
back of a length, Zaman plays away from his body and chops an inside edge past his stumps, short fine leg cuts it off
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: leading edge, just out of reach in Mahmood's follow-through! Touch fuller, nibbling as Zaman closes the face, squirts it back past the non-striker's stumps for a single
short, cramps him with the ball coming in, short-armed to mid-on - tidy opening over from Mahmood
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: bowled 'im through the gate! Moeen finds his line from round the wicket straight away, and he topples Zaman with his first ball! Nicely flighted but this didn't turn, as the batsman was expecting, simply scuttled on with the arm and into the top of middle stump. Good night!
over the wicket, tossed up and clipped through mid-on for his first international run
darted on the stumps and Azam nudges another back down the ground
Haider goes boom! Second ball launched over wide long-on! He has absolutely melted that, down on one knee and slogging aggressively through the line
Commentary_short: Ali to Haider Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: pushed through and tucked off the pads
floated up outside off, Azam opens the face on a drive in front of square
length in the channel and steered down to third man
angled in and worked off the body behind square
creamed down the ground! Imperious from Azam, stroking this on the up back through mid-off and away
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: carted through midwicket, back-to-back fours for the captain! Dug in by Mahmood but the ball sits up nicely and he swings it away through the infield
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: filleted to third man! Three in a row for Babar, sits back and angles the face on a cross-seamer, gets the ball fine, third man is back but can't get across to cut it off
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: short of a length, this time Azam stays back and glides one to third man
full on off, 82mph/132kph and spanked on the drive, Jordan grabs it in his follow through
Commentary_short: Jordan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tight line outside off, Azam again looks for the angled bat glide and chops it down into the turf
Commentary_short: Jordan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: 86mph/138kph and steered through backward point, good running brings them two on the throw
length, 83mph/134kph and sliding into the pads, Azam tucks through backward square
short and in at the hip, Haider swings across the line, deflects towards third man off the body
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haider Ali, 1 leg bye

Commentary: shortish length and worked away through the leg side, just a single, decent start from Jordan
full and fast, up in the blockhole and Azam can only bunt to mid-on
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: castled! Curran goes straight through Pakistan's captain and talisman! Perfect length, Azam a little flat-footed as he aimed a wafty drive, and the ball hit the seam before coming back and properly jiggering his stumps! *Powerplay wicket klaxon* England have a second for the night
pitched up, skidding on to the pads, tucked towards short fine leg
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: short, pulled from outside off, single to deep square leg
bangs in the bumper wide of off stump, Haider bottom-edges a pull through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Curran to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: still a flak in that! Mr Whippy wrists from Haider as he ices a Curran half-volley through midwicket to the fence! Decent over nevertheless
Commentary_short: Curran to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: length on the stumps, tucks him up and Hafeez can only jab one to mid-on
short outside off, Haider bottom-edges this to fine leg! Makes his own luck with a hack across the line, skitters away past the man on the edge of the ring
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: rammed through backward square, he's got hold of that! Cramped for room but those hands came through so quickly, sends a rasping pull to the long boundary
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: shortish and forced away off the back foot
pitched up, Hafeez is forward and gently taps into the covers
Commentary_short: Jordan to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: slower ball, I think, and he's through the shot early, chipped towards extra cover... doesn't quite carry to the England captain, Morgan
Commentary_short: Jordan to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: fullish and driven down the ground coming forwards on off stump
length, 84mph/136kph and heading leg side as Hafeez swings to leg... there was a sound, umpire Michael Burns says 'not out', but no wide signalled. Flicked the pad
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: panhandled over midwicket! Fetches a pull in front of deep square, almost goes all the way... first boundary for Hafeez
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: length outside off, maybe a slower ball and this is guided to third man
angled in on the stumps and nudged for one
short ball, loopy bouncer through to the keeper as Hafeez ducks it
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: Haider tees off straight away! Length ball on the pads, Haider swings gleefully to leg, holds his shape like Tiger aiming for the fairways... All the way over the long boundary at deep midwicket! Yeesh!
Commentary_short: Gregory to Haider Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: skidding through outside off, angled behind square
short and wide, 78mph/126kph and flogged through the infield to deep cover
short of a length, skidding on as Haider pulls along the carpet for one
swung into the leg side and they think about coming for two, Billings fires in a throw... it's then misfielded, but still England manage to keep them to one
short and down the leg side - called
pitched up, 72mph wide of off stuimp and Haider settles for a slice through backward point for one more
pushes this through quite wide of the stumps, loosener from Rashid and it's cut behind deep point for a couple
drops short, Haider goes back on his stumps and flicks through backward square leg
bit of flight, this spins away as Haider reaches out and dabs for one

flat outside off, cut hard behind point and it looks to be rolling to the boundary marker... until Gregory throws himself full length to pull the ball in! <del>Top work in the deep, I think</del> Still four because his knee was touching the rope (although it requires multiple replays to confirm)
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: tossed up and slapped down the ground to long-on
googly, tucked off the stumps through midwicket
driven hard but he picks out mid-off
Commentary_short: Gregory to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: clubbed leg side, the long part of the ground again... clears the leaping Sam Billings at deep midwicket! Did Billings misjudge it? He seemed a long way in, the ball went yards over his head in the end, bouncing away for four
Commentary_short: Gregory to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: shortish and angled to third man playing back
short and swung away behind square on the leg side, Banton does well to cut it off but they hare back for two
bouncer, 80mph/129kph and climbing through wide of the stumps... Hafeez wanted the extra there
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: good slower ball to finish, deceives him as it spins through under the bat, not far from shaving off stump
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: ooh err, loses his line here, wide of the cut strip and spinning further past Bairstow for a couple
appeal for lbw, big heave across the line from Hafeez... spinning too much, maybe? Michael Burns not interested and England don't review
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: clipped down the ground to long-on
tossed up and punched back past the bowler again
smoked like a breakfast mackerel! Floated up full, Hafeez picks the Bosie and slog-sweeps it over deep midwicket for six
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: launched again! Skips out to this one, doesn't allow the ball to turn away from him, banged high over deep square leg... he's lost the ball this time!
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: a good one, pushed through and spinning away, low past Hafeez's cross-batted swipe through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: short ball on off, Haider pulls it through square leg for one
sashays down, looking to boom this back down the ground... misses a cutter flung wide of the stumps
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: shortish and Hafeez bottom-edges this through backward square leg
slower ball on the stumps, Haider watches it closely and clips uppishly through midwicket into a gap
back of a length, misses out looking to swipe off his hip
Commentary_short: Gregory to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: cracked in front of square on the pull, finds the boundary, fifty on debut for Haider Ali! Played beautifully on his first outing, raises the bat to his team-mates. First man to do so for Pakistan in T20Is, living up to his billing as a bright young thing
Commentary_short: Gregory to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: short of a length outside off and he dabs one to third man
slower ball from Curran, beats Haider's attempted moosing over the leg side, big ole swing and a miss
Commentary_short: Curran to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: fired full on off and punched for one through the covers
Hafeez doing sixy bits again! Short and wide of off, Curran is trying to stop him hitting there... but no such luck as Hafeez goes back and across and fetches it over deep midwicket once again!
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: pace on bouncer, 80mph/129kph wide of the stumps and he swats it through the leg side again
flung full and wide and Haider can't lay bat on this
Commentary_short: Curran to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: tossed up and skidding into the pads, Hafeez swinging for the fences but fails to connect
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: fires this flat and quick down the leg side
looks to do him in the flight, Hafeez on the charge again... Nailed straight! Six more for the Professor, who's giving another tutorial tonight. Pinged over long-on!
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: flighted, Hafeez goes for the reverse-swipe over cover, 'catch that!' yelps Bairstow... but doesn't carry
floats this up full down the leg side, spins through past the stumps as he attempts another slog-sweep
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: hoicked over midwicket on the sweep, this is going to skip away between two fielders set back leg side... Half-century for Hafeez, fourth in his last five T20I innings for Pakistan
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: pushed through and he can't connect playing back
Commentary_short: Rashid to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: full on the stumps, clipped through midwicket
full and wide, 84mph/135kph and dragged through the leg side, century stand up between these two

bowled full pint! Off stump is flattened by a fizzing yorker, and Haider's fun on debut is over! Jordan hits the target with one that tails back in at pace with Haider looking to clear the front leg... Still, he's announced himself to the world in fine style, has Haider Ali

fired in full straight again, squeezed out behind point... England review for lbw, but that's hit the middle of the bat! Quickly turned down by Alex Wharf, the TV umpire, and England lose one of their two reviews
speared wide of the stumps at 86mph/138kph and Hafeez can't lay bat on it
Commentary_short: Jordan to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: full toss, 82mph/132kph and mistimed into the midwicket area... was it above waist height? Not deemed so by the on-field umpires, but looked close to me
another full toss, swung behind square on the leg side, Rashid has to run around
that's a high full toss, flung raggedly down the leg side, YJB does well to prevent it running for four
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, (no ball) 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, full outside off and Shadab slogs without timing to long-on
just clears mid-off, tonking the slower ball down the ground for a welcome boundary!
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: short ball, pulled behind square
back of a length again, maybe pace off and Shadab misses with a back-foot carve
Commentary_short: Gregory to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: gets this away over backward point! On his toes and opening up to play this late behind square, gets it through the infield and will pick up four!
Commentary_short: Gregory to Shadab Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: heaves a full toss into the stands! Deliverooed for six, a standing wallop as Curran misses his length
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: full and quick on off stump, dug out for one
full toss, 82mph, this time Shadab can only scoop one back over the bowler's head
goes full and wide, jams down for one through gully
slower ball, Shadab swings like big bad Benny Goodman but only manages a bottom edge into the leg side
length ball, paddled away through square leg from outside off - 11 off the over but could have been worse for Curran after that start
pitched up and dragged into the leg side, they'll only get one
pitched up and following Shadab as he steps to leg, clipped out to deep midwicket
hacked over the leg side, between deep midwicket and deep backward square for two
full on leg stump, not quite in the blockhole but Hafeez can only swing one to deep midwicket
swiped over backward square leg! Shadab gets his second boundary with a funky flip, bottom handing this between two men back on the rope
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Shadab Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: full length, 87mph/139kph and he chips this into a gap at wide long-on
attempted yorker, slightly too full... caressed for six! Jordan only just missed his mark there, but Hafeez took it on the full and whispered it back down the ground, all the way!
Commentary_short: Jordan to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: dropped! Hammered through the off side, Morgan can't quite reel it in... Flings himself to his right at extra cover, got one hand to the ball, couldn't cling on!
full outside off, Shadab goes across his stumps and misses with a cheeky ramp
Commentary_short: Jordan to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: bunted to mid-off! Jordan gets another, Shadab picking out Curran for a simple catch... didn't quite land the yorker but it does the job, couldn't get under the ball
Dismissal_text: Shadab Khan c Curran b Jordan 15 (25m 11b 2x4 0x6) SR: 136.36

Commentary: dropped! Imad slogs a slower delivery straight up, looks to be a simple catch coming in from long-on, but Curran shells it this time! Into the hands and out again
heaved through the leg side, they'll get a couple to Curran at wide long-on this time
pitched up, 84mph/136kph in the slot and pounded down the ground to long-on
over the wicket to the lefty, sprayed wide of the tramlines
fired across the bows again, Imad carves a top edge down to third man
goes for the blockhole again, Hafeez swats a full toss down the ground and comes back as long-on runs around
length outside off, cutter from Mahmood, Hafeez sets himself but can't get it past the man at cover
angled across on a length, 84mph/136kph and Imad whacks it along the ground to the cover sweeper

dropped? Think it went straight through Mahmood in his follow through, the ball squeezes past mid-off but long-on comes around... so Hafeez equals his highest T20I score and England will need 191 to win the game and the series
tight line, bit of swing back into the right-hander, tucked off the hip to midwicket to get off the mark
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: shaping across Bairstow's bows, left alone with a flourish as it climbs through to Sarfaraz
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: yeehaw! Fuller length, outside off, Bairstow plants the front foot and has a monster munch outside off, but catches only thin air
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: snorter! Outswing, outswing, inswing ... timber! An exceptional yorker, Bairstow blinks in bafflement as he trudges off with his stumps rattled. He hardly saw that, but he heard it alright! Shaheen is gleeful, and Pakistan are in the game!
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, OUT
Dismissal_text: JM Bairstow  b Shaheen Shah Afridi 0 (4m 3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: a flat-footed waft as Shaheen dangles a back-of-a-length ball outside off. No contact. A big opportunity for Malan ...
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, no run

Commentary: on the back foot, flashed down to third man with an open face, and finds enough of a gap to pick up a couple
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, 2 runs

Commentary: advancing to the pitch, but gets too close to the pitch, and squeezes his drive into the covers
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, no run

Commentary: standing firm in the crease this time, trying to open the face into the covers
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, no run

Commentary: round the wicket once more, and flogged with intent, clean through the covers! He reached that on the full, and timed the pants off it
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: reverse sweep, and he's nailed it! No messing around from Banton here, picking his stroke early and battering it hard through backward point
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: galloping to the pitch again, Imad sees him coming and fires it in flatter. Blocked in a hurry
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, no run

Commentary: another reverse sweep, but so close to the fielder this time! Inches short of the man at backward point, who made the ground but pulled out at the last second as he yorked himself. Precious runs for England
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: hustled on the back foot, defended into the off side as Malan is squared up in defence
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, no run

Commentary: a flat-footed slap, and Malan gets away with a leading edge! Cramped for room on the carve as Shaheen follows him into the body, at 89mph, and the shot plops in no-man's land at backward point
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, 1 run

Commentary: beaten off the pitch, perfect seam, hitting the deck outside off and nibbling past the outside edge
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: back of a length, cracked hard but not timed back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: flogged once again, back down the pitch, England just putting bat through ball at the moment, with no real plan against some sharp pace
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: whistles through to the keeper! Proper fast bowling this, hitting the deck and leaping past the splice. Lively effort!
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, no run

Commentary: pounded with oodles of lovely bottom hand! Banton is sized up his options, and reckons Imad must go! Right to the pitch and tonked through wide long-on!
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: another skip to the pitch, another fast, flat response, scuffed to the on-side
biffed off a good length, but straight to square leg. A precious dot
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, no run

Commentary: that's not a dot! Tossed up wider, outside off, and Malan rifles his drive, on the up and clean through extra cover. Shot
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: Imad comes round the wicket, and ... that's a fine catch on the edge of the rope! It's the shorter leg-side boundary, Malan was cramped on the slog-sweep but rightly felt the shot was on, and a few more inches would have sufficed! Instead it's a well-timed leap, and another precious breakthrough!
Dismissal_text: DJ Malan c Fakhar Zaman b Imad Wasim 7 (14m 8b 1x4 0x6) SR: 87.50

Commentary: on the back foot, shovelled to the on-side, 'only one!' is the yakka from Sarfaraz behind the stumps. Lots of hustle from Pakistan in the field
c-r-u-n-c-h-e-d through the covers! A stride to the pitch, and a lovely crispy drive into the gap. Like a firm young carrot...
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: thumped in short, energetic from Rauf as Banton claws a pull around the corner, and into the gap at backward square
very full, thumps the pad as Banton sets off for a single, and Morgan gets into a tangle with Rauf as he turns back for a quick single. All very innocent, and on we go
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, no run

Commentary: banged in short, but it doesn't get up, and Banton lays his pull in the line of the ball, and the pace does the rest, through backward square
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: squeezed from a full length, down into the pitch, Banton digging out the attempted yorker with every part of his stance
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, no run

Commentary: flipped through fine leg, and it's an no-ball for the full-toss as well... free hit coming up!
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, (no ball) FOUR runs

Commentary: a stand-and-deliver tonk to the on-side, but can't quite pick the gap. Still, Banton is on one again
on the back foot, boshed into the covers without much timing. 85mph first-up ...
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Banton, no run

Commentary: Banton gallops across his crease, looking to flip the ball over his shoulder, but doesn't make contact this time
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Banton, no run

Commentary: flicked up and over midwicket, and Morgan spots the opportunity for two early. Good running to keep England ticking
battered off a good length, hard through midwicket, baseball style. Plugs five feet short of the fielder... and another free hit coming up!
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Banton, (no ball) 1 run

Commentary: panned on the up, over long-off. Wahab just about gets away with that one
on the back foot, open face through third man
fractionally off-line and a little too short, Banton eases it off the hips through fine leg and rattles into the 40s
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length, turning into the left-hander, who wafts a defensive slap out to cover
biffed off the back foot, climbing into the width, hitting with the spin out to deep cover, and cut off in the deep with a tumble
another slap into the covers, but can't find the gap
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Banton, no run

Commentary: a cuffed pull, not timed, and picked up at long-on
fired down the leg side to ruin an otherwise tidy over
and that's properly ruined it! Legbreak, tossed into Morgan's arc, and out comes that familiar contemptuous slam, up and over midwicket!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, SIX runs

Commentary: run out! A terrible mix-up! Morgan wanted the run, Banton turned it down late. The skipper is utterly stranded and Pakistan are cockahoop! They needed that! A slap into the covers, Babar gathered quickly and spooked the non-striker. Oops
Dismissal_text: EJG Morgan run out (Babar Azam/†Sarfaraz Ahmed) 10 (18m 5b 0x4 1x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: into the toes, clipped to midwicket, to bring the formless Moeen into the firing line...
pushed across the left-hander, a slapped drive down to third man to get off the mark
on the hips, whipped to the on-side without much timing
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, 1 leg bye

Commentary: fuller length, angled across Moeen who hops back to prod a block out to point

so full and thuds the pad! Oh my, that is excruciatingly close, and Pakistan review! It was coming in with the arm, had to be hitting on or around off stump... I reckon it'll be at least umpire's call on line... maybe even smashing off. Smashing it is! A fine review to end a fine innings. Banton can't atone for running out his captain, and now Pakistan are right in the hunt!
Dismissal_text: T Banton lbw b Haris Rauf 46 (40m 31b 8x4 0x6) SR: 148.38

Commentary: poked into the covers... England have the challenge their lower-middle order has been waiting for...
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Billings, no run

Commentary: nudged off the legs to the on side
pressed into the covers, another single as Billings finds his range
prodded to the on-side once more
twirled onto an excellent length outside off, firmly blocked back to the bowler
eased out to point off the back foot, this is a very placid over for Pakistan, as they tighten the noose on this mid-innings
flapped off the back foot, and finds the gap! A fraction too short from Shadab, Billings' heart was in his mouth for a moment as deep midwicket lurked, but he nailed it well enough
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Billings, FOUR runs

Commentary: opens the face on the back foot, to third man. Moeen content to nurdle for the moment as he tries to rediscover his touch
jabbed off the back foot, down into the gully. Sharp pace from Wahab to keep the new batsmen hopping
whipped with more of a flourish from Moeen, but the same upshot, a single to deep square leg
flinched back to the bowler as Wahab hits the deck just back of a length again
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Billings, no run

Commentary: too short and leg-sided, and excellent from Billings, picking off the pull with a roll of the wrists behind square. Valuable runs in tight times for England
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Billings, FOUR runs

Commentary: crashed firmly into the covers, climbing into the width, and a misfield allows a tight single to be completed without any fuss
premeditated from Billings, Imad sees him coming and fires it wider, drilled into the covers
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Billings, no run

Commentary: two-step and launched! High and handsome, right underneath the stroke, and high into the stands at wide long-on!
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Billings, SIX runs

Commentary: on the back foot, clattered out to deep cover

round the wicket, and Sarfaraz misses a slow-motion stumping! Extraordinary moment, Moeen charged, missed a quick ball, gave up on getting back to the crease, but Safaraz took an age to gather and couldn't break the stumps!
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Ali, no run

Commentary: eased down to long-off
flashed with intent to long-on. A life for England in that over, will it be the moment to liven up Moeen?
advancing to the pitch, can't get the ball away
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Billings, no run

Commentary: another charge, fenced out to cover for another single
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Billings, 1 leg bye

Commentary: right under the drive, high out to deep extra cover, an in-form Moeen would have smoked that into the stands. This version is just glad to have another ball to find his range...
fired out wider as Moeen shimmies at the crease, cut to deep point
attempted reverse sweep, very wide line, 'very well bowled Shadab' says Sarfaraz, and who are we to argue
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Ali, no run

Commentary: this time he nails the reverse! Shadab took Sarfaraz's praise a touch too literally, and tried the same ball again. This time Moeen was waiting with a slot through backward point!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: advancing to the pitch, can't quite get there
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Billings, no run

Commentary: reverse sweep again, and Sarfaraz is flummoxed by the flurry of limbs, and lets the ball through his gloves
pumped into the covers, lots of bottom hand
very wide of off stump, but gets away with it
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Billings, no run

Commentary: wide yorker, that's a lovely ball at this stage, Billings can only toe-end it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Billings, no run

Commentary: wide again, but a full toss this time. Flogged hard into the covers
pounded off a good length! Moeen swings through the line, hard over long-on. Right in his arc that time...
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: here comes Moeen! Lifted with disdain, high and hard over extra cover, guiding the stroke with a subtle late adjustment of the wrists. When he nails it, my word ... it is nailed
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: flapped off the fuller length through backward point, one hand coming off the stroke as he does so
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, 1 run

Commentary: zipping through to the keeper, scuttling a touch as Billings can't connect
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Billings, no run

Commentary: a baseball slap around the corner, no timing but plenty of placement as fine leg has to make ground to gather
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Billings, 2 runs

Commentary: banged in short, and that's an excellent bouncer, Billings stays motionless, hoping for the wide, but that zipped through to the keeper. Shaheen claws his third over back well
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Billings, no run

Commentary: slower yorker, that's an excellent ball, tailing into Moeen's toes and demanding that he gave up his aggressive intent to save his timbers. 68mph there...

much quicker, and a wild swipe steeples to third man! Billings had no say over the destiny of that ball, a keen mow to hack out the full length, and a well-judged take. The needle moves once more, as Lewis Gregory enters for a big test of his mettle
Dismissal_text: SW Billings c Imad Wasim b Wahab Riaz 26 (29m 24b 2x4 1x6) SR: 108.33

Commentary: left-arm round, right into Moeen's ribs, but that's a cunning slower ball, as Moeen tucks up in defence, only to flick his pull behind square
pushed onto the back foot, 87mph, and Gregory hops back and across to block
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Gregory, no run

Commentary: back of a length again, angled into the right-hander, tucked into the covers to get Moeen back on strike
opens the face for a glide to third man, if he'd timed it any better he'd have holed out, instead it plugs ten feet short for a single
panned clean into the stands! Out comes the googly, picked like a freshly scrumped apple! High over the bowler's head!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: back to back sixes! Another plant of the front foot, another swing of the blade, battered out over wide long-off!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: wider line, Moeen yawns into a cut, but can't make contact... a precious dot!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Ali, no run

Commentary: dragged down and smoked over midwicket! Moeen advanced, Shadab responded, and responded with a long-hop! This is Moeen, back at the party!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: faster and flatter, chipped to the on-side for the single
full length, whipped on the up to midwicket. That was the over England needed!
back of a length, clubbed with a resounding echo of bat, but timed too well as deep midwicket gathers
slower ball, well disguised, Moeen scuffs his clip high in the air, but safe at midwicket, and that's a 25-ball fifty! Tidy...
full toss, not quite high enough to be a no-ball, but high enough for Gregory to cloth his wipe through the line. High on the splice and gathered at mid-on
drilled hard along the turf to long-off. It's been a good response so far this over...
wide full toss and that's the boundary! Well timed from Gregory, just oodles of bottom-handed power, belting the cross-seamer over wide mid-on. And Rauf is a very cross seamer after that...
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Gregory, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball, a cutter in the slot, picked by Gregory who slams his drive clean over the umpire's head! A big finish to the over, and suddenly England scent a chance
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Gregory, FOUR runs

Commentary: full length, wide line, flashed through third man with a calculated edge! England keep on coming...
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower-ball legcutter, Moeen has a wipe and misses, Sarfaraz fumbles but they can't take the single
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, no run

Commentary: yorker, but just a fraction too wide, and Moeen's response is exquisite! Opens the face, those wrists to the fore, and times the stroke beautifully through backward point
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: length delivery, crunched over short cover, but short of long-off... he's timing them well now...
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ali, 1 run

Commentary: bowled him! Gregory gives himself room for an unsubtle thwack through the line, but he can't pick the legcutter. He's through the shot too soon, and back goes his middle stump. Still, a lively hand in the circumstances...
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Gregory, OUT
Dismissal_text: L Gregory  b Shaheen Shah Afridi 12 (18m 8b 2x4 0x6) SR: 150.00

Commentary: tight line, a genuine edge, and Sarfaraz parries a certain four! Scoops a non-catch to third man, as Jordan settles for the single. Thus ends a fine spell from Shaheen. The end of an tough series for him, ever-present in all contests for Pakistan, Tests as well
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Jordan, 1 run

Commentary: fired down the leg side! That's very handy for England...

very full length, poked to the off side, and though Jordan is quick, Wahab is every bit as rapid! A rapid gather in his followthrough, a turn and shy, and he nails the stumps with the batsman two inches short! A huge wicket. Moeen is back on strike, but Jordan can clear the ropes when he needs to...
Dismissal_text: CJ Jordan run out (Wahab Riaz) 1 (5m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: round the wicket, slower ball, Moeen settles for a dabbed single into the gap on the off side
flashed down to third man, solid contact on the wider line
zippy length, through to the keeper, Moeen was shuffling and shimmying at the crease, so he just fired it out wide and took the dot
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Ali, no run

Commentary: round the wicket, Moeen is cramped on the pull and Wahab snaffles the top-edge in his followthrough! A sharp bouncer ends a superb innings. Is it enough to keep England in the hunt though? England need to get busy off this final ball of the over!
Dismissal_text: MM Ali c & b Wahab Riaz 61 (60m 33b 4x4 4x6) SR: 184.84

Commentary: round the wicket, Curran attempts a back-flick over the keeper but can't connect. What a game-turning over that was! England need 17 off the final over... or 16 for the Super Over!
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Curran, no run

Commentary: a swing and a miss! Right in the arc for the mow, but misses out. England sprint the single and a direct hit would have been curtains for Curran
yorker, excellent length, chiselled back over the bowler's head but mopped up by long-off
swinging into the toes, battered to the leg side. They rush back for two, but the challenge is getting dicey now...
dinked off the face of the bat as Rashid hops across his crease... England need two sixes now...
back of a length, and launched over the covers! Curran has monstered that, high and hard! Well well ... it's still on!
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Curran, SIX runs

Commentary: that's the length! A wide yorker, and Curran can't connect!
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Curran, no run
